To manually create a bibliography environment,

@verbatim
  \begin{thebibliography}{<widest tag>}
  \bibitem[<<tag>>]{<unique>}
  \end{thebibliography}
@end verbatim

Depending on the document class, either @code{\bibname} prints `Bibliography'
or @code{\refname} prints `References'.@*
@code{thebibliography} environment automatically invokes either @code{\bibname} or @code{\refname}, and then prints the bibitems.@*

@code{\cite[<<text>>]@{<unique>@}} cites the reference.

Most classes dont add the bibliography to the TOC.@*
KOMA-Script classes have the option @code{bibliography=totoc|totocnumbered}.@*


